      "raw_text": "Deck X. Welt, in complaint filed\nin the superior court, alleges that on\nSeptember 13, 1898, Charles l.. Nc\nKenzie executed to him a promissory\nnote for $1,000, payable in five years\nwith interest at the rate of 10 per\ncent per annum and l per cent\nmonth after maturity. securing the\nsame by mortgage on certain\nrealty.\n\n\nPayment OF interest upon the note\nis acknowledged up to September,\n1900, but no other payment of either\ninterest or principal. it is alleged,\nwas made after that date. Other de-\nPENDANTS are named in the suit and\nthe plaintiff demands foreclosure and\nthe sale of the mortgaged premises\nTO satisfy the claims:"
    }
  ]
